 Instance variables :-
    are variables declared inside a class but outside methods.
    They belong to each object, so every object has its own copy.

 Instance methods :-
    are non-static methods that work on instance variables.
    They need an object to be called.


 âœ… If they ask follow-up:

 Q: How are instance variables different from static variables?
 A: Instance variables belong to objects (each object has its own copy), while static variables belong to the class (shared by all objects).

 Q: How do you call an instance method?
 A: Using an object reference, like s1.display();.